&lt;p&gt;Do you have any further questions here or can this ticket be closed?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="22429" author="johann" created="Thu, 3 Nov 2011 12:25:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; At CEA they have a weird situation where a user presumably has only 8 GBs of data, whereas the quota commands report a usage of several TBs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have you tried to run quotacheck?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; So we would like to know where the quota information is stored by Lustre:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Space accounting is handled by ldiskfs itself. Operational quota files on the slaves (i.e. MDT &amp;amp; OSTs) are available at the root under lquota_v2.user and lquota_v2.group. As for administrative quota files (i.e. stored on the MDT which is the quota master), there are under the OBJECTS directory and the file names are admin_quotafile_v2.usr &amp;amp; admin_quotafile_v2.grp.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
